### ============ VEHICLES CRUD ============

### Create vehicle (ownerId = 1, customer must exist)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/vehicles
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "plateNumber": "А123БВ777",
  "model": "Toyota Camry",
  "year": 2020,
  "ownerId": 1
}

### Create vehicle 2
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/vehicles
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "plateNumber": "В456ГД777",
  "model": "Honda Civic",
  "year": 2019,
  "ownerId": 1
}

### Get all vehicles
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/vehicles

### Get vehicle by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/vehicles/1

### Get vehicles by owner (business operation)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/vehicles/by-owner/1

### Update vehicle
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/vehicles/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "plateNumber": "А123БВ777",
  "model": "Toyota Camry",
  "year": 2021,
  "ownerId": 1
}

### ============ SERVICE ORDERS CRUD ============

### Create service order (vehicleId=1, customerId=1, mechanicId=1, partIds=[1,2])
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/service-orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "vehicleId": 1,
  "customerId": 1,
  "mechanicId": 1,
  "partIds": [1, 2],
  "laborCost": 5000.00,
  "requiredTasksCompleted": false
}

### Create service order 2 (without parts)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/service-orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "vehicleId": 2,
  "customerId": 1,
  "mechanicId": 1,
  "laborCost": 3000.00,
  "requiredTasksCompleted": true
}

### Get all service orders
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/service-orders

### Get service order by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/service-orders/1

### Update service order
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/service-orders/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "vehicleId": 1,
  "customerId": 1,
  "mechanicId": 2,
  "partIds": [1, 2],
  "laborCost": 5500.00,
  "requiredTasksCompleted": true
}

### ============ BUSINESS OPERATIONS ============

### 1. Calculate order total (parts cost + labor)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/service-orders/1/total

### 2. Add parts to order (decreases stock, single transaction)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/service-orders/2/parts
Content-Type: application/json

[1, 3]

### 3. Get customer service history
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/service-orders/by-customer/1

### 4. Get mechanic's open orders (workload)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/service-orders/by-mechanic/1/open

### 5. Close order (requiredTasksCompleted must be true)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/service-orders/1/close

### Verify: Get order total after close
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/service-orders/1/total

### Verify: Get mechanic's open orders (order 1 should be closed now)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/service-orders/by-mechanic/1/open

### ============ DELETE (cleanup) ============

### Delete service order
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/service-orders/2

### Delete vehicle
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/vehicles/2

### Delete part
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/parts/3

### Delete mechanic
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/mechanics/2

### Delete customer
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/2
